OL,3,CPolice ability to protect public will
OL,4,C'erode' without investment
OL,6,FMr Boutcher was addressing the monthly
OL,7,Fpublic meeting of the Policing Board,
OL,8,Fthe oversight body of the PSNI, where
OL,9,Fhe said without additional investment
OL,10,Fand an uplift in officer numbers, his
OL,11,Fability to protect the public would
OL,12,Fcontinue to "erode".
OL,14,FHe was responding to a report
OL,15,Fpublished this week by His Majesty's
OL,16,FInspectorate of Constabulary and Fire
OL,17,F& Rescue Services (HMICFRS) which
OL,18,Ffound that continued financial
OL,19,Fpressures facing the force are likely
OL,20,Fto continue to affect the service it
OL,21,Fprovides if left unresolved.
OL,26,@tD@MOUtD@SO]
