OL,3,CPolice ability to protect public will
OL,4,C'erode' without investment
OL,6,F"Our ability to respond to this report
OL,7,Fand to implement the policing plan
OL,8,Frelies not just on our officers and
OL,9,Fstaff, but far more at this moment in
OL,10,Ftime on the support of this board,
OL,11,Fgovernment, partners and communities
OL,12,Fto secure necessary funding and
OL,13,Fresources that we require.
OL,15,F"When I arrived as Chief Constable,
OL,16,Fseeing the position the organisation
OL,17,Fhad been allowed to deteriorate to, as
OL,18,Fregards its numbers, I commissioned an
OL,19,Findependent group to assess what the
OL,20,Fpolice officer numbers should be.
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@AOU
